# Supply-chain lockdown (#67 P0-1a). This is a hot wallet: a malicious dependency `postinstall`
# runs with full ambient authority in the same install as the seed-holding offscreen bundle, so a
# single compromised (or typo-squatted) dep could exfiltrate keys at `npm install` time. Deny ALL
# dependency lifecycle scripts by default; only the hand-reviewed allowlist in
# `allowed-install-scripts.json` is re-run afterwards, via `npm run allow-scripts`. `scripts/allow-scripts.mjs`
# also fails the build if any UNLISTED dependency ships an install script (drift → a review gate).
# Never remove this line without also removing the allow-scripts gate.
ignore-scripts=true
